verbose_text: In order to confirm whether recognition of bacterial components by PMNs from diabetic subjects was impaired, we investigated their ability to produce IL-1beta and IL-8 after stimulation with defined TLR ligands; LPS and flagellin are recognized by TLR4 and TLR5 respectively, and TNF-alpha.
evidence: produce IL-1beta and IL-8 after stimulation with defined TLR ligands; LPS and flagellin are recognized by TLR4 and TLR5 respectively, and TNF-alpha
